      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Manners are a concern for JILLIBY AURA (2) after she broke as a hot favourite in last week's heat but the prior form was very strong, winning fresh at Bendigo before a close second in the G1 NSW Trotters Oaks. Very well served by the low draw and has the class to beat these if she gets it right. ALDEBARAN ADA (5) capitalised on JILLIBY AURA's mistake to win last week's heat. Had been close to that filly in her other two starts this time in, finishing only 1.7m behind her when she placed in the Oaks two back. Draws wider than she has of late but she is going well and is reliable. DESIRING DIAMONDS (3) draws well and could be hitting her peak at the right time having stuck on to place last week. HALLEBESOFINE (7) draws wide but did well to finish second to ALDEBARAN ADA last week and has scope for further improvement third up.",
